The area of this region is given by: \[ \text{Area} = 2 \times \text{Length} \times 1 + \pi \times 1^2 = 2 \times 5 + \pi = 10 + \pi \] 3. **Approximation and Rounding**: The value of \(\pi\) is approximately \(3.1416\). Therefore, the area of \(\mathcal{R}\) is approximately: \[ 10 + 3.1416 \approx 13.1416 \] The integer closest to \(13.1416\) is \(13\). Thus, the integer closest to the area of \(\mathcal{R}\) is \(\boxed{13}\).
